Basic query:
```typescript
const result = await client.ontology.objects.Contract
  .where(Contract.status.eq('ACTIVE'))
  .orderBy(Contract.startDate.asc())
  .fetch({ pageSize: 100 });
```
The result contains a data array (the current page) and a nextPageToken if more pages exist.
Pagination handling:
- Check result.nextPageToken; if present, make another fetch call with { pageToken: result.nextPageToken }
- For full dataset iteration, use a loop or a generator function:
```typescript
async function* fetchAllContracts() {
  let pageToken: string | undefined;
  do {
    const page = await client.ontology.objects.Contract
      .fetch({ pageSize: 200, pageToken });
    yield* page.data;
    pageToken = page.nextPageToken;
  } while (pageToken);
}
```
Performance considerations:
- Do not fetch all pages before rendering; render the first page immediately and load additional pages lazily as the user scrolls
- Apply server-side filters before fetching; do not fetch all objects and filter client-side
- Cache page results if the data does not change frequently; avoid re-fetching on every component re-render
